This program is SHAREWARE!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  The menu-projects created by this unregistered version of "MMEditor"
  are showing a requester at every start.

  If you like M&M and you plan to use the menus created with it,
  you have to register.

  After registration, you will get a dongle-file which will prevent
  the requesters from appearing.


What is it all about?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  With Menus & More (M&M) you are able to create graphic orientated
  screen menus. Once you have installed your own menu, you can easily
  call many programs from one central screen. It's like designing your
  own workbench.

  Because of the great amount of options, you are able to produce
  even more than just menus - as the name of program indicates!


How can I install M&M?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  For installation purpose start the menu-project "First!.M&M"
  by double-clicking.

  If you want to look at the projects in the "Examples" drawer,
  you have to assign the logical device "MM:" to the M&M drawer.
  You can do this by

    - calling First!.M&M
    - calling the shell and typing

        1> assign MM: MyHardDisk:Tools/M&M

        (it is assumed that the M&M drawer are stored in a directory
        called "Tools" on a device called "MyHardDisk")


How can I get more information about M&M?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  You can access more information by starting "MMEditor" and
  pressing the HELP key. The M&M documentation guide will appear.

  If you have questions, please write to me - but include a SAE!


